messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Files containing the implementation of App\Http\Controllers\UserController::show

- app/Http/Controllers/UserController.php

Explanation
- routes/web.php imports App\Http\Controllers\UserController and registers Route::resource('users', UserController::class)->only('show'), so the route will call the show method on that exact class.
- I inspected the controller file app/Http/Controllers/UserController.php and confirmed it implements:
  - public function show(Request $request, User $user): View
  - It returns the users.show view with the passed User model and several counts and recent posts/comments (posts_count, comments_count, likes_count, latest 5 posts with likes/comments counts, latest 5 comments with post author).
- I also located other controllers named UserController (app/Http/Controllers/Admin/UserController.php and app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/UserController.php) but those are in different namespaces (App\Http\Controllers\Admin and App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1) and are not the class imported by routes/web.php, so they are not the target here.
